<br>
I absolutely love the idea of being able to summon one of each kind of focus item but here are the problems:<br>
<br>
1. Cast time is too long 10 seconds compared to 6 seconds for the single item summons. Now I know that this is still a time saving in most cases to casting multiple 6 second spells, *but* this is an upgrade to the single item summon spells. The 10 second cast time is painfully slow in a raid situation.<br>
<br>
2. Difficulty in summoning. By this I mean the problem of the focus items being LORE along with the fact that the items are summoned *inside* the satchel. For me, this meant that I had two problems. First, I had to summon my items last - comined with the problem stated in (1), I was still summoning while the raid got underway and could get none of the benefits of having my own focus items whilst continuing to summon items for others. Second, many folks had no bag inventory slots free - an obvious pain.<br>
<br>
I see three solutions to this problem.<br>
<br>
First and IMO best is to make all spells that summon LORE objects targetable, just like the new trans rod spell. This would enable mages to use /rtarget as well as being able to wear focus items whilst summoning for others.<br>
<br>
Second would be to have the bag summon in the same manner as the Kunark era multi object summons - ie, container, then each object, one at a time a la Gift of Xev. <br>
<br>
Third and IMO worst idea is to have some kind of auto-drop functionality.<br>
<br>
<br>
My apologies if this has previously been discussed. I doubt that it will be addressed by VI, but I had to get it off my chest. This made me absolutely crazy the other night!  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
